- Use Spring Boot's auto-configuration to reduce boilerplate code.
- Structure your application using layers (Controller, Service, Repository).
- Leverage Spring Profiles for environment-specific configurations.
- Use @Transactional for managing transactions effectively.
- Always use an ORM (like Hibernate) to connect with PostgreSQL for better abstraction and easier data manipulation.
- Implement proper exception handling using @ControllerAdvice.
- Use Spring Profiles for environment-specific configurations.
- Leverage Spring Security for authentication and authorization.
- Keep your services stateless to improve scalability.
